Unless we are to suppose with Breiter that Gronovius (who was very unlikely to do so) mistook a fifteenth-century MS. for one of sace. xi, and that the M readings have come into Ven. actually from lis, then we can only explain our facts by deriving Ven. from some MS. of the GL type which occasionally preserved more faithfully than GL the reading of the archetype.
